title: For Sale:  Marlin 782 WMR  US ARMY VET Discount
postcontent:
Make: Marlin 

Model: Model 782 

Serial Number: 19779238 

Year of Manufacture: 1977 

Caliber: .22 W.M.R. (Winchester Magnum Rimfire) 

Action Type: Bolt Action Rifle, w/ Detachable Box Magazine 

Markings: The left side of the barrel is marked "THE MARLIN FIREARMS CO. NORTH HAVEN, CT. U.S.A. / MODEL 782 -- MICRO-GROOVE BARREL -- CAL. 22 W.M.R. ONLY", and has a "JM" contained in an oval. The left side of the receiver is marked "19779238". The right side of the barrel is marked with the safety "warning". 

Barrel Length: 22" 

Sights / Optics: This rifle is mounted with a brass bead post style front sight dovetailed into a ramp, with a detachable hood. The rear sight is the standard fold down semi-buckhorn with elevator. The receiver is grooved to take clamp on scope mounts. Scope attached is a Tasco 4x15, perfect for sighting varmints and small game. 

Stock Configuration & Condition: The one piece stock is WALNUT (not a laminate or picture of walnut ), with impressed checkering on the pistol grip and the forearm areas. The comb of the butt stock is Monte Carlo style and there is a Marlin hard black plastic butt plate with white spacer. The stock is fitted with sling swivels, sling is attached, and has the traditional Marlin "Bullseye". The LOP measures 13 ¾" from the front of the trigger to the rear of the butt stock. The stock has no chips or cracks and no marks. The stocks rate EXCELLENT PLUS overall condition. 

Type of Finish: Blue 

Finish Originality: All Original 

Bore Condition: The bore is bright and the Micro-Groove rifling is sharp. There is NO erosion, DEEP BLUING is as it was purchased originally, the muzzle crown is unmarked. 

Overall Condition: This rifle retains about 99% of its metal finish. The balance of the finish shows wear at the sharp edge of the scope mounts. The Screw heads are sharp. The markings are clear. Overall, this rifle rates EXCELLENT PLUS condition. 

Mechanics: The action functions correctly. Rifle has been fired about 50 rounds, 30+ years ago, and will hit a dime, dead center, at 100 yards. Cleaned and oiled every 6 months for 37 years. 

Box, Paperwork & Accessories: An official Marlin leather carrying sling is provided. The sling is in Fine condition with only a few scuff or compression marks. There is also one unmarked magazine which functions correctly. Also comes with a Weather Shield tan leather carry case, model # 1291, Made in the U.S.A., also in EXCELLENT condition. 

Assessment: This Marlin looks as if it may never have been fired, but since it was, I can not sell it as new. Stored it very carefully in a humidity controlled display case in Michigan with other collectables. This rifle appears "like new". Chambered in .22 W.M.R. this rifle is an excellent gun for pests or small varmint control, particularly when out fitted with a scope. This rifle will make a fine present for a young man learning to shoot with the best rifle he will ever own, or for a collection piece of Marlin Rifle history. It is without a doubt the best rifle I have ever owned, all parts made in the U.S.A. and assembled in the U.S.A.

postcontent: I have a old Solid steel Hopkins & Allen Revolver, Its considered a Relic/Antique because it's just so old, to be exact the Firearm was made in 1901, as I had It looked at and authenticated years ago When I inherited it. Everything still Works and is all original part wise, It has a nice chrome finish and about 80percent of the finish remains. it also has it's original grips with the nice Hopkins&ALlen Logo on them. Its a 6 shot cylinder with a 4inch octagonal barrel. The barrel was so pitted and beat and recently at my home I shot 2 blanks out of my Hopkins&Allen Revolver and the last blank I fired the bore fractured in 2 places. The Bore has a hair line fracture on the top and on the bottom of the Barrel. I was told by a qualified Gun Smith that the bore / barrel can be yanked off and replaced with another Hopkins&Allen .32 S&W centerfire chambered barrel or He said I could just have him create a barrel to replace the Original. It's not a Super pricey fix as everything else still works and is almost in new Condition as I've babied my Hopkins&Allen Revolver since I've owned it, it's been in my Revolver collection for years. My Revolver says Right on top of the frame above the cylinder, Model #6 and in big letters it says Double Action. Before the bore fractured, I've personally only fired S&W .32 regular "shorts" thru it even though I was told by a Qualified Gun Smith some years ago I could safely fire the more powerful .32 smith and wesson Longs, he just said you can but don't have to. I'm looking for a value of at least 70dollars for the project Revolver and a value of about 30dollars for the ammo and the Blanks, so about 100bucks total for everything. Also when I brought my revolver to be checked after the bore split / fractured I asked the Gun Smith if it had anything to do with the ammo or the blanks and he clearly stated to me as I thought, the bore really couldn't handle much more because of it being so pitted and Old. I never had the smith take the barrel off yet Because I figure it's still a great gun with life left and just needs some work and you'll basically have a new Rvolver. I have about 40 to 45 .32 S&W blanks to scare pests off and for training under noise/pressure, and I have around 30 to 35 rounds of .32 regular, "shorts", Their 82grain LRNs bullets Made by Untied State Cartridge Company. title: For Sale:  NIB S&W 360J, M360J, Smith & Wesson 360 J, .38 Special, Scandium Frame, RARE & UNIQUE
postcontent:
Brand New in Box, Unfired, Rare .38 Special version of the Scandium frame model 360. This is the M360J, or 360J, not the M&P 360 or the 360PD. Those are .357 Magnum, and were common production guns. This Airweight, as noted by the placement of the serial number under the cylinder release (also inside the crane as with all S&W revolvers), is a unique limited run from S&W, and was for Japanese Law Enforcement, but a few were sold in the States. They are tough to come by and this one is brand new. Weighs exactly 14.82 ounces. 5 shot, .38 Special, and modern day .38 Special S&W revolvers can shoot +P, just not +P+. I have dry fired it, the double action is typical of S&W J frame revolvers, but the single action is ultra light and crisp! This revolver looks like a mini version of the Night Guard, a discontinued S&W revolver that was built on the L and N frames, so not quite as concealable as this 360J.

Call or text with serious inquiries only please, $600 cash, no trades, valid FOID, Bill of Sale and 72 hr. wait required. If from out of State, shipping to FFL only, $40 FedEx 2 day insured, and your FFL must receive shipments from private sellers.

Hi, I have an upper I am looking to sell. Here are the specs:

VLTOR VIS Carbine monolithic upper receiver. The upper receiver and rail are one single        piece. There rail is all one perfect piece from back to front. No gap.
YHM 14.5 inch fluted barrel with a pinned and welded muzzle brake.
YHM flip up gas block front m4 sight with sling adapter
SCT nickle boron bolt carrier group. Carrier is made of 8620 steel. Bolt is MPI/HPT 158 carpenter steel. 
Strike industries extended charging handle. 

This is basically an upgraded m4 rifle upper, with a 14.5 inch barrel and a carbine length rail. Every single part on the upper is brand new purchased for this build, and assembled at PT Firearms in Cross Plains. Rail panels are already installed on both sides. I have a Magpul XTM kit on the bottom of the rail, If you would prefer a Magpul AFG2 instead, let me know. For those unaware, barrels must be 16 inches for the gun to be legal. anything under a 16 inch barrel is considered a short barreled rifle. The one way to get around this is to have the muzzle brake pinned and welded to the barrel. This means if you wanted to change the brake you would have to go to a gunsmith. I see no reason to do so, as it is a good brake and tuned to the barrel perfectly by YHM, but I wanted to clarify that. Please don't make offers, I have over $1150 into this and it is new and unused. Also, I am not looking for trades on this, I am selling because I need money. If you would like to attach it to a lower to test it and have a place to do so, let me know.
